<HEADLINE>
FT  07 DEC 93 / Teachers urge SIB action on pensions
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By JOHN GAPPER
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
The Association of Teachers and Lecturers yesterday called for the
Securities and Investments Board to take immediate action to help up to
27,000 teachers who have opted out of their occupational pension scheme in
the past five years, John Gapper writes.
The union's call followed the disclosure that the SIB plans to launch an
inquiry into possible unnecessary sales of personal pensions to up to
500,000 former members of occupational schemes.
Mr Peter Smith, ATL general secretary, has written to Mr Andrew Large, SIB
chairman, calling for insurance companies to be instructed to examine every
pension policy issued to a teacher.
</TEXT>
