<HEADLINE>
FT  07 DEC 93 / World Trade News: Italy agrees Dollars 1.6bn Russian gas
package
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
A state-backed Dollars 1.6bn (Pounds 1.07bn) finance package paving the way
for equipment sales by Italian companies to Russia's gas industry was signed
in Rome yesterday, Robert Graham reports from Rome.
The 13 1/2 -year credit, organised by the state credit institute,
Mediocredito Centrale, in conjunction with Banca Commerciale, will be
covered by Sace, the export credit guarantee organisation. The main
suppliers will be two subsidiaries of ENI, the state oil concern - Nuovo
Pignone and Snamprogetti.
Italian companies will modernise part of the old Soviet gas production and
supply system, with payment through gas supplies. Some equipment is to be
produced in former Russian military plants.
