<HEADLINE>
FT  07 DEC 93 / Australian mill strike
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By NIKKI TAIT
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   SYDNEY
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Strike action yesterday hit three crushing mills operated by Bundaberg
Sugar, the Australian sugar group which was acquired by Britain's Tate &amp;
Lyle, writes Nikki Tait in Sydney.
The action is thought to involve 700-800 workers, and to be related to
current enterprise-based pay talks. The employees are believed to have begun
an overtime ban on Friday, and moved to full strike action yesterday,
despite industrial relations commission hearings in Queensland.
</TEXT>
<XX>
