everyone in this room, everyone on this island, needing to learn totally new
stuff in the next 60 months'. He is American, of course. Still, he certainly
seems to have his own business skills sorted out: the BBC is promoting his
video, price Pounds 395 plus VAT (7.20).
Ken Livingstone claims that when asked to play himself, in tonight's episode
of the embarrassingly naff Woman's Guide To Adultery on ITV, he specified
'No nude scenes with Amanda Donohoe'. How politically correct can you get?
(9.00).
Panorama reports on new government figures which suggest that racial attacks
in Britain are more common than hitherto assumed (9.30 BBC1).
