FT  04 DEC 93 / Finance and The Family: Directors' transactions - The Budget
and You
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By COLIN ROGERS, The Inside Track
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Regalian Properties has been hurt by the property decline but business is
picking up and three board members including the chairman and chief
executive and finance director have all bought stock, increasing their
stakes considerably.
Kenwood Appliances came to the market in July 1992 and has performed
strongly since. Following the interim results,,six board members have sold
stock at 316p. Each retains a sizeable number of shares.
Forward has been a strong performer over the past 12 months, outperforming
the market by more than 158 per cent. Interim results showed good growth. In
May, the chairman and chief executive sold stock at 223p. Since then, the
shares have shown further increases to trade around 230p level. P. Starkey
is another director to take advantage of the price increase and sold stock
shortly after coming to the main board.
